<subSubSection id="DFC86578FFF8D70DFF7D9E9DFD21F8AE" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="976D36F3FFF8D70DFF7D9E9DFEE2F968" blockId="5.[151,1437,1692,1907]" box="[151,270,1692,1717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="A5A6EAE1FFF8D70DFF7D9E9DFEE2F968" box="[151,270,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="976D36F3FFF8D70DFF2C9EC0FB8AF8DD" blockId="5.[151,1437,1692,1907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Forewing length 16.5 mm. Forewing upperside cell spots conjoined, lower one larger and rounded; spot in space CuA 
<number id="211A24D4FFF8D70DFEFC9EF7FEF2F8D9" box="[278,286,1782,1796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
largest, narrow, basally oblique, distally concave; without male stigma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="976D36F3FFF8D70DFF2C9F0FFD21F8AE" blockId="5.[151,1437,1692,1907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="0FE92A76FFF8D70DFE949F0FFDFCF8F5" box="[382,528,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 − 41" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1120,1144]" captionTargetBox="[172,1399,469,1094]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,439,1115]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 37 − 41. Male genitalia of Scobura evansi Devyatkin (Guangdong). 37. ring, lateral view; 38. tegumen, dorsal view; 39. valva, inner view; 40. aedeagus; 41. juxta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195594/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figs. 
<number id="211A24D4FFF8D70DFE2A9F0FFDFCF8F5" box="[448,528,1806,1832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="39.0" valueMax="41.0" valueMin="37.0">37−41</number>
</figureCitation>
): Tegumen without socius; uncus thin and long; saccus short and broad; valva with ventrodistal process pointed distally; aedeagus with suprazonal sheath slightly shorter than subzonal sheath; juxta U-shaped and each arm bifurcated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
